parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
and warning lights may appear on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in repairing recalled airbag systems can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights may appear on the instrument panel
and the vehicle may be unable to have the recall repair completed due to parts unavailability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag control module can prevent airbags from deploying in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights may appear on the instrument panel
and the airbag system may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked exhaust manifolds can cause carbon monoxide to leak into the vehicle's cabin, posing a significant risk to the health and safety of occupants. Additionally, a cracked manifold can lead to decreased engine performance and potentially cause engine damage.
symptoms: Exhaust fumes or carbon monoxide leaking into the cabin
cracked or broken exhaust manifold
rust or corrosion on the exhaust system
decreased engine performance
loud exhaust noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Exhaust System Design Flaw and Rusting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A flawed design of the exhaust system can lead to premature rusting and failure, causing exhaust leaks and potentially releasing harmful gases into the environment.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the exhaust system
tailpipe rusted off at the flange behind the muffler
exhaust hanger failure
loud exhaust noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handle can cause the door to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to exit or enter the vehicle, which can be a safety hazard in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door handle stops working from inside or outside
the door cannot be opened or closed
the door latch mechanism fails to engage
the door flaps open and cannot be closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust pipe connection can cause the tailpipe to become detached, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The exhaust pipe connection rusts through
the tailpipe becomes loose or detached
the vehicle shakes or vibrates while driving
the connection piece between the muffler and tailpipe corrodes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the exhaust system can cause the tailpipe to fall off while driving, creating a road hazard and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Rusted and cracked exhaust manifold
rusted connection between muffler and tailpipe
tailpipe dangling from the bottom of the truck.
